{"parentUuid":"fbefb34e-a2d9-44bb-ab59-907f0f213199","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a8eaafaa5ba8f955e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WH8CxsnJJN2MQqjakJd4HX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# DGC Terminal Interface — Definitive Component Architecture\n     2→\n     3→**Version:** 1.1 — Provider-Agnostic  \n     4→**Date:** 2026-03-05  \n     5→**Baseline:** v1.0 (2026-03-05) — Claude-specific architecture  \n     6→**Target:** Python Textual 8.0.2 + Any LLM provider (Claude, OpenAI, OpenRouter, Ollama, custom)  \n     7→**Platform:** macOS M3 Pro, Python 3.14  \n     8→**Status:** Architecture Blueprint — Ready for Implementation\n     9→\n    10→---\n    11→\n    12→## Table of Contents\n    13→\n    14→1. [Architecture Diff vs v1.0](#1-architecture-diff-vs-v10)\n    15→2. [ProviderAdapter Interface](#2-provideradapter-interface)\n    16→3. [Canonical Normalized Event Schema](#3-canonical-normalized-event-schema)\n    17→4. [Capability Matrix & Graceful Degradation](#4-capability-matrix--graceful-degradation)\n    18→5. [Provider-Neutral Session Store](#5-provider-neutral-session-store)\n    19→6. [Concrete Provider Mappings](#6-concrete-provider-mappings)\n    20→7. [Governance & Safety Layer](#7-governance--safety-layer)\n    21→8. [Revised Package Structure](#8-revised-package-structure)\n    22→9. [Preserved TUI UX Goals](#9-preserved-tui-ux-goals)\n    23→10. [2-Week Implementation Plan](#10-2-week-implementation-plan)\n    24→11. [Phase-1 Code Prompt for Claude Code](#11-phase-1-code-prompt-for-claude-code)\n    25→\n    26→---\n    27→\n    28→## 1. Architecture Diff vs v1.0\n    29→\n    30→### What Stays (v1.0 foundations preserved)\n    31→\n    32→| v1.0 Component | Status | Notes |\n    33→|----------------|--------|-------|\n    34→| Decomposed package with hard boundaries | **KEPT** | Structure refined, not replaced |\n    35→| `engine/` has zero Textual imports | **KEPT** | This was the best decision in v1.0 |\n    36→| One widget per file | **KEPT** | — |\n    37→| Screens as composition, not behavior | **KEPT** | — |\n    38→| Theme as separate concern (TCSS) | **KEPT** | — |\n    39→| Message bus architecture | **KEPT** | Event types change; bus pattern stays |\n    40→| Warm dark amber theme (Appendix B) | **KEPT** | Verbatim from v1.0 |\n    41→| Keyboard binding map | **KEPT** | — |\n    42→| Widget inventory (18 components) | **KEPT** | StatusBar gets provider-aware fields |\n    43→| Phased build approach | **REVISED** | Resequenced around adapter-first |\n    44→| RichLog-based StreamOutput | **KEPT** | Consumes canonical events, not raw provider events |\n    45→| TextArea multi-line PromptInput | **KEPT** | — |\n    46→| Widget registry for Darwin | **KEPT** | — |\n    47→| Stigmergy bridge hooks | **KEPT** | — |\n    48→\n    49→### What Changes\n    50→\n    51→| v1.0 Component | v1.1 Change | Why |\n    52→|----------------|-------------|-----|\n    53→| `engine/stream_parser.py` (Claude NDJSON only) | **REPLACED** by `engine/adapters/` package with per-provider adapters | v1.0 hardcoded `parse_ndjson_line()` for Claude's wire format |\n    54→| `engine/subprocess_manager.py` (Claude Code process) | **REPLACED** by `engine/provider_runner.py` dispatching to adapter's `start()`/`stream()` | v1.0 assumed subprocess + NDJSON stdout; OpenAI/Ollama use HTTP SSE/NDJSON |\n    55→| `engine/event_types.py` (Claude-shaped dataclasses) | **REPLACED** by `engine/events.py` with canonical schema v1 | v1.0 had `SystemInit.mcp_servers`, `AssistantMessage.parent_tool_use_id`, etc. — Claude-specific fields |\n    56→| Appendix A (Claude NDJSON protocol) | **MOVED** to `engine/adapters/claude.py` docstring | Protocol details belong with the adapter, not the architecture doc |\n    57→| `~/.claude/sessions/` session browser | **REPLACED** by `~/.dharma/sessions/` with provider metadata | v1.0 tied to Claude Code's session storage |\n    58→| `StatusBar` fields | **REVISED** — `model` → `provider:model`, add provider badge | Must show which provider is active |\n    59→| Event routing table | **REVISED** — routes canonical events, not Claude NDJSON types | Left column changes from `system/init` → `session_start`, etc. |\n    60→| Build sequence | **RESEQUENCED** — Phase 0 now includes adapter interface + Claude adapter | Adapter is the foundation, not an afterthought |\n    61→\n    62→### What's New in v1.1\n    63→\n    64→| New Component | Purpose |\n    65→|---------------|---------|\n    66→| `engine/adapters/` package | Abstract `ProviderAdapter` + concrete adapters |\n    67→| `engine/adapters/base.py` | `ProviderAdapter` ABC + `ModelProfile` + `ProviderCapabilities` |\n    68→| `engine/adapters/claude.py` | Claude Code CLI adapter (subprocess + NDJSON) |\n    69→| `engine/adapters/openai.py` | OpenAI Responses API adapter (HTTP SSE) |\n    70→| `engine/adapters/openrouter.py` | OpenRouter adapter (OpenAI-compatible SSE) |\n    71→| `engine/adapters/ollama.py` | Ollama local adapter (HTTP NDJSON) |\n    72→| `engine/events.py` | Canonical normalized event schema v1 |\n    73→| `engine/session_store.py` | Provider-neutral session persistence |\n    74→| `engine/governance.py` | Permission boundaries, redaction, audit log |\n    75→| `engine/provider_runner.py` | Replaces `subprocess_manager.py` — dispatches to adapters |\n    76→| `config/providers.toml` | Provider configuration (keys, endpoints, defaults) |\n    77→\n    78→---\n    79→\n    80→## 2. ProviderAdapter Interface\n    81→\n    82→### Design Principles (Stolen from the Best)\n    83→\n    84→| Source | Pattern Stolen | Why It's Right |\n    85→|--------|---------------|----------------|\n    86→| Vercel AI SDK `LanguageModelV3` | Two methods: `doGenerate()` + `doStream()` | Minimal surface = fewer bugs, easier to implement new adapters |\n    87→| pydantic-ai `ModelProfile` | Declarative capability matrix drives behavior | No runtime `if provider == \"claude\"` conditionals scattered through the codebase |\n    88→| aisuite `provider:model` string | Single string identifies provider + model | Clean config, clean CLI, clean UI display |\n    89→| Mirascope `@call` decorator | Provider is a parameter, not a class hierarchy | Runtime swappability without inheritance acrobatics |\n    90→| Instructor `Mode` enum | Output strategy depends on provider capabilities | Graceful degradation: tools → json_schema → markdown |\n    91→\n    92→### Abstract Base\n    93→\n    94→```python\n    95→# engine/adapters/base.py\n    96→from __future__ import annotations\n    97→from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n    98→from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n    99→from typing import AsyncIterator, Any\n   100→from enum import Flag, auto\n   101→\n   102→from ..events import CanonicalEvent, SessionStartEvent\n   103→\n   104→\n   105→class Capability(Flag):\n   106→    \"\"\"Provider capability flags. Queried before use, never assumed.\"\"\"\n   107→    STREAMING       = auto()\n   108→    TOOL_USE        = auto()\n   109→    THINKING        = auto()  # Extended thinking / reasoning tokens\n   110→    VISION          = auto()\n   111→    JSON_SCHEMA     = auto()  # Structured output via schema\n   112→    PARALLEL_TOOLS  = auto()  # Multiple tool calls in one turn\n   113→    RESUME          = auto()  # Resume a previous session\n   114→    COST_TRACKING   = auto()  # Per-request cost data available\n   115→    CONTEXT_USAGE   = auto()  # Reports tokens used / remaining\n   116→    SYSTEM_PROMPT   = auto()  # Supports system messages\n   117→    CANCEL          = auto()  # Can cancel in-flight request\n   118→\n   119→\n   120→@dataclass(frozen=True)\n   121→class ModelProfile:\n   122→    \"\"\"Immutable capability snapshot for a specific model.\"\"\"\n   123→    provider_id: str\n   124→    model_id: str\n   125→    display_name: str                         # e.g. \"Claude Sonnet 4.5\"\n   126→    capabilities: Capability = Capability(0)\n   127→    max_input_tokens: int | None = None\n   128→    max_output_tokens: int | None = None\n   129→    cost_per_input_mtok: float | None = None  # USD per million input tokens\n   130→    cost_per_output_mtok: float | None = None\n   131→    supports_temperature: bool = True\n   132→    default_temperature: float | None = None\n   133→    extra: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)  # Provider-specific metadata\n   134→    \n   135→    def supports(self, cap: Capability) -> bool:\n   136→        return bool(self.capabilities & cap)\n   137→\n   138→\n   139→@dataclass\n   140→class ProviderConfig:\n   141→    \"\"\"Configuration for a provider instance.\"\"\"\n   142→    provider_id: str               # \"claude\", \"openai\", \"openrouter\", \"ollama\"\n   143→    api_key: str | None = None     # None for Ollama (local)\n   144→    base_url: str | None = None    # Override default endpoint\n   145→    default_model: str | None = None\n   146→    extra: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n   147→\n   148→\n   149→@dataclass\n   150→class CompletionRequest:\n   151→    \"\"\"Provider-agnostic request. Adapters translate to wire format.\"\"\"\n   152→    messages: list[dict[str, Any]]\n   153→    model: str | None = None           # Override adapter's default\n   154→    system_prompt: str | None = None\n   155→    tools: list[dict] | None = None\n   156→    tool_choice: str | dict | None = None\n   157→    temperature: float | None = None\n   158→    max_tokens: int | None = None\n   159→    stop_sequences: list[str] | None = None\n   160→    enable_thinking: bool = False      # Request reasoning if available\n   161→    resume_session_id: str | None = None\n   162→    provider_options: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)  # Escape hatch\n   163→\n   164→\n   165→class ProviderAdapter(ABC):\n   166→    \"\"\"Abstract interface every provider must implement.\n   167→    \n   168→    Contract:\n   169→    - __init__ receives ProviderConfig only\n   170→    - start() is called once at session start\n   171→    - stream() yields CanonicalEvents — the ONLY output type\n   172→    - Adapters NEVER import Textual or any UI code\n   173→    - Adapters are unit-testable with zero external dependencies\n   174→    \"\"\"\n   175→    \n   176→    def __init__(self, config: ProviderConfig) -> None:\n   177→        self.config = config\n   178→    \n   179→    @property\n   180→    @abstractmethod\n   181→    def provider_id(self) -> str:\n   182→        \"\"\"Stable identifier: 'claude', 'openai', 'openrouter', 'ollama'\"\"\"\n   183→        ...\n   184→    \n   185→    @abstractmethod\n   186→    async def list_models(self) -> list[ModelProfile]:\n   187→        \"\"\"Return all available models with capability profiles.\"\"\"\n   188→        ...\n   189→    \n   190→    @abstractmethod\n   191→    async def get_profile(self, model_id: str | None = None) -> ModelProfile:\n   192→        \"\"\"Return capability profile for a specific model (or default).\"\"\"\n   193→        ...\n   194→    \n   195→    @abstractmethod\n   196→    async def stream(self, request: CompletionRequest) -> AsyncIterator[CanonicalEvent]:\n   197→        \"\"\"Stream a completion request. Yields canonical events.\n   198→        \n   199→        This is the primary execution method. Even non-streaming providers\n   200→        yield at minimum: session_start, text_complete, usage, done.\n   201→        \"\"\"\n   202→        ...\n   203→    \n   204→    async def cancel(self) -> None:\n   205→        \"\"\"Cancel in-flight request. Default: no-op.\"\"\"\n   206→        pass\n   207→    \n   208→    async def close(self) -> None:\n   209→        \"\"\"Release resources (HTTP clients, subprocesses). Called on shutdown.\"\"\"\n   210→        pass\n   211→```\n   212→\n   213→### Adapter Lifecycle\n   214→\n   215→```\n   216→┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   217→│            ProviderRunner                      │\n   218→│                                                │\n   219→│  1. Load config from providers.toml            │\n   220→│  2. Instantiate adapter: ClaudeAdapter(cfg)    │\n   221→│  3. profile = await adapter.get_profile()      │\n   222→│  4. Check capabilities → adjust UI             │\n   223→│  5. events = adapter.stream(request)           │\n   224→│  6. async for event in events:                 │\n   225→│       post_message(AgentEvent(event))          │\n   226→│  7. await adapter.close()                      │\n   227→└──────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n   228→```\n   229→\n   230→---\n   231→\n   232→## 3. Canonical Normalized Event Schema\n   233→\n   234→### Design: Envelope + Typed Payload\n   235→\n   236→Every event shares an envelope. The `type` field is the discriminator. Version field enables future evolution without breaking consumers.\n   237→\n   238→```python\n   239→# engine/events.py\n   240→from __future__ import annotations\n   241→from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n   242→from typing import Any\n   243→import time\n   244→\n   245→SCHEMA_VERSION = 1\n   246→\n   247→@dataclass\n   248→class CanonicalEvent:\n   249→    \"\"\"Base envelope for all events in the DGC event bus.\n   250→    "}]},"uuid":"b88146de-05a6-47b9-a216-bde54c3a6d1f","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:30.698Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"fbefb34e-a2d9-44bb-ab59-907f0f213199","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
