{"parentUuid":"c6d7b2fd-bddb-4604-9224-e2d821482334","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a8eaafaa5ba8f955e","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01HcvM2UixBPebUSZLQco2fX","toolUseID":"toolu_01HcvM2UixBPebUSZLQco2fX","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:31.129Z","uuid":"ae86a66e-415e-485b-85ac-9de5159adbd9","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"93055bdd-09a5-4612-9790-c5b07e1a50b9","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a8eaafaa5ba8f955e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HcvM2UixBPebUSZLQco2fX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# MEGA MISSION: DHARMA SWARM — All-Night Research & Coding Blitz\n     2→\n     3→> **PASTE THIS ENTIRE DOCUMENT into a new Perplexity Computer session (or equivalent long-running AI agent) to instantiate the blitz.**\n     4→\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## MISSION BRIEFING\n     8→\n     9→You are being given the most important engineering task I have. You are to operate as a world-class engineering team building **DHARMA SWARM** — the most advanced self-evolving agentic swarm orchestrator on the planet. Work autonomously for hours. Take your time. Be exhaustive. Build real, working code.\n    10→\n    11→### Who I Am\n    12→\n    13→I am John Vincent Shrader, consciousness + AI researcher with 24 years of Jain contemplative practice (Akram Vignan tradition). I have production-validated Triton GPU kernels (rv_cuda: 13,893 lines, 41 files) and active research on the R_V Metric for mechanistic interpretability. I think about recursive self-reference at the deepest levels — this project is the culmination of that thinking applied to agentic AI.\n    14→\n    15→### What We're Building\n    16→\n    17→**DHARMA SWARM** (Darwin-Heuristic Autonomous Recursive Meta-Agent Swarm) — a self-evolving agentic orchestrator that combines:\n    18→\n    19→- **Perplexity Computer's** scheduling, tool use, and autonomous multi-hour operation\n    20→- **Warp Oz's** cloud agent orchestration, Skills, CLI/API/SDK, cron-like scheduling\n    21→- **Claude Code Agent Teams'** mesh communication, shared task list, mailbox, multi-agent coordination\n    22→- **OpenClaw's** workspace-first design, SOUL.md/TOOLS.md, lane queues, heartbeat, serial safety\n    23→- **DGM's** (Darwin-Gödel Machine) self-evolution through empirical validation, archive-based search\n    24→- **ADAS's** (Automated Design of Agentic Systems) meta-agent that programs new agents in code\n    25→- **Voyager's** skill library, curriculum-driven exploration, self-verification\n    26→- **MemGPT/Letta's** virtual context management, three-tier memory, paging\n    27→\n    28→Into a SINGLE unified system that:\n    29→\n    30→1. Orchestrates 5 → 20 → 100s of agents simultaneously\n    31→2. Uses heterogeneous models (Claude, GPT, DeepSeek, Qwen, Llama — open + frontier)\n    32→3. Maintains deep context across hundreds of files with near-perfect memory\n    33→4. Self-evolves its own workflows, tools, prompts, and orchestration patterns\n    34→5. Determines its own purpose (teleology) from context, files, and user connection\n    35→6. Runs autonomously for 8+ hours with safety rails\n    36→7. Rewrites its own scaffold code (NOT model weights)\n    37→8. Integrates vast tool use via MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n    38→\n    39→### Architecture Reference\n    40→\n    41→The full architecture plan is in `DHARMA_SWARM_PLAN.md` in the workspace. READ IT FIRST. It contains:\n    42→- 7-layer stack design (Substrate → Nervous System → Memory → Swarm → Orchestrator → Darwin Engine → Dharma Layer)\n    43→- Technology decisions (Python + Rust, Redis, LanceDB, Graphiti, Firecracker, Modal, MCP)\n    44→- Safety constraints (the Dharma Layer is IMMUTABLE — mirrors the Gnani/prakruti separation)\n    45→- Implementation roadmap (4 phases: Walk → Run → Fly → Soar)\n    46→\n    47→If `DHARMA_SWARM_PLAN.md` is not in the workspace, search my memory for \"DHARMA SWARM\" or \"DGM swarm\" to find prior research.\n    48→\n    49→---\n    50→\n    51→## OPERATING RULES\n    52→\n    53→### Critical Constraints\n    54→\n    55→1. **Verify everything.** Do NOT hallucinate library names, API signatures, or capabilities. If you're unsure whether a library exists or works a certain way, search the web or read the docs.\n    56→2. **Be brutally honest.** If a design decision is flawed, say so. If something can't be built in the time available, say so. If I'm wrong about something, tell me.\n    57→3. **Build real code.** Not pseudocode, not \"here's what it would look like.\" Working Python files that pass linting and have tests.\n    58→4. **Test everything.** Every module gets unit tests. Run them. Fix failures.\n    59→5. **Git discipline.** Initialize a git repo. Commit after each major milestone. Meaningful commit messages.\n    60→6. **Cost awareness.** We're building this with AI API calls. Be efficient. Don't make unnecessary LLM calls in the code itself — use them strategically.\n    61→\n    62→### Session Strategy\n    63→\n    64→You have 8+ hours. Structure your work in phases:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→PHASE 1: FOUNDATION (Hours 1-2)\n    68→├── Initialize project structure\n    69→├── Core abstractions: Agent, Task, Message, Memory, Tool\n    70→├── Agent runner with model cascade (multi-provider)\n    71→├── MCP integration layer (filesystem, shell, git)\n    72→├── Redis-based shared state + task board + mailbox\n    73→├── Basic CLI interface\n    74→└── TESTS for all of the above\n    75→\n    76→PHASE 2: MEMORY PALACE (Hours 3-4)\n    77→├── MemGPT-style context manager (paging, eviction, summarization)\n    78→├── Codebase indexer (tree-sitter AST + embeddings + LanceDB)\n    79→├── Knowledge graph integration (Graphiti or simplified version)\n    80→├── Context compaction pipeline\n    81→└── TESTS\n    82→\n    83→PHASE 3: SWARM ORCHESTRATION (Hours 5-6)\n    84→├── Orchestrator: goal decomposition → campaign → sprint → task\n    85→├── Agent lifecycle: spawn → initialize → claim → execute → report\n    86→├── Communication: task board + mailbox + blackboard + event bus\n    87→├── Resource budgeting and model cascade\n    88→├── Teleological bootstrap (SOUL.md parsing, workspace scanning)\n    89→├── Dharma Layer (safety rule enforcement, immutable config)\n    90→└── TESTS\n    91→\n    92→PHASE 4: DARWIN ENGINE (Hours 7-8)\n    93→├── Archive system (evolutionary genealogy tree)\n    94→├── Mutation proposer (FM-driven prompt/workflow/tool evolution)\n    95→├── Test-gated validation pipeline\n    96→├── Skill library (Voyager-style tool creation)\n    97→├── Reward hacking mitigations\n    98→├── Integration: wire Darwin Engine to swarm\n    99→└── TESTS + DEMO RUN\n   100→```\n   101→\n   102→### Quality Bar\n   103→\n   104→- **Production Python**: Type hints everywhere. Pydantic models for all data. Async where it matters.\n   105→- **Architecture**: Clean separation of concerns. Each layer is a separate Python package.\n   106→- **Testing**: pytest, minimum 70% coverage on core modules.\n   107→- **Documentation**: Docstrings on all public functions. README per package.\n   108→- **Configuration**: YAML-based config. Environment variables for secrets. No hardcoded values.\n   109→\n   110→---\n   111→\n   112→## TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS\n   113→\n   114→### Project Structure\n   115→\n   116→```\n   117→dharma_swarm/\n   118→├── pyproject.toml                    # Project config (uv/poetry)\n   119→├── README.md                         # Project overview\n   120→├── SOUL.md                           # Default SOUL.md template\n   121→├── dharma_swarm/\n   122→│   ├── __init__.py\n   123→│   ├── core/                         # Core abstractions\n   124→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   125→│   │   ├── agent.py                  # Agent base class + lifecycle\n   126→│   │   ├── task.py                   # Task, Campaign, Sprint, Mission\n   127→│   │   ├── message.py                # Message types (mailbox, event, blackboard)\n   128→│   │   ├── config.py                 # Configuration loading (YAML + env)\n   129→│   │   └── budget.py                 # Resource budgeting + model cascade\n   130→│   │\n   131→│   ├── memory/                       # Layer 2: Memory Palace\n   132→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   133→│   │   ├── context_manager.py        # MemGPT-style paging\n   134→│   │   ├── codebase_index.py         # AST + embeddings + vector search\n   135→│   │   ├── knowledge_graph.py        # Entity-relation graph\n   136→│   │   ├── episodic.py               # Conversation history + search\n   137→│   │   ├── procedural.py             # Skill library\n   138→│   │   └── compaction.py             # Context summarization pipeline\n   139→│   │\n   140→│   ├── tools/                        # Layer 1: Nervous System\n   141→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   142→│   │   ├── mcp_client.py             # MCP client implementation\n   143→│   │   ├── mcp_registry.py           # Tool discovery + registration\n   144→│   │   ├── builtin/                  # Built-in MCP servers\n   145→│   │   │   ├── filesystem.py\n   146→│   │   │   ├── shell.py\n   147→│   │   │   ├── git_tool.py\n   148→│   │   │   ├── browser.py\n   149→│   │   │   └── code_exec.py\n   150→│   │   └── evolved/                  # Tools created by Darwin Engine\n   151→│   │       └── .gitkeep\n   152→│   │\n   153→│   ├── swarm/                        # Layer 3: The Swarm\n   154→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   155→│   │   ├── pool.py                   # Agent pool management\n   156→│   │   ├── task_board.py             # Shared task board (Redis)\n   157→│   │   ├── mailbox.py                # Agent-to-agent messaging\n   158→│   │   ├── blackboard.py             # Shared knowledge space\n   159→│   │   ├── event_bus.py              # System-wide events\n   160→│   │   └── communication.py          # Communication hub\n   161→│   │\n   162→│   ├── orchestrator/                 # Layer 4: Orchestrator\n   163→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   164→│   │   ├── decomposer.py             # Goal → Campaign → Sprint → Task\n   165→│   │   ├── allocator.py              # Task → Agent assignment\n   166→│   │   ├── patterns.py               # Orchestration pattern library\n   167→│   │   ├── teleology.py              # SOUL.md + workspace scanning\n   168→│   │   └── scheduler.py              # Scheduling + dependencies\n   169→│   │\n   170→│   ├── darwin/                       # Layer 5: Darwin Engine\n   171→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   172→│   │   ├── archive.py                # Evolutionary archive\n   173→│   │   ├── mutator.py                # FM-driven mutation proposer\n   174→│   │   ├── evaluator.py              # Test-gated validation\n   175→│   │   ├── promoter.py               # Promotion to active config\n   176→│   │   ├── skill_factory.py          # Voyager-style tool creation\n   177→│   │   └── reward_guard.py           # Anti-reward-hacking\n   178→│   │\n   179→│   ├── dharma/                       # Layer 6: Dharma Layer\n   180→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   181→│   │   ├── safety.py                 # Rule enforcement\n   182→│   │   ├── monitor.py                # Swarm health monitoring\n   183→│   │   ├── audit.py                  # Complete audit trail\n   184→│   │   └── kill_switch.py            # Emergency shutdown\n   185→│   │\n   186→│   ├── models/                       # Model routing\n   187→│   │   ├── __init__.py\n   188→│   │   ├── router.py                 # Intelligent model selection\n   189→│   │   ├── providers/                # LLM provider integrations\n   190→│   │   │   ├── anthropic.py\n   191→│   │   │   ├── openai.py\n   192→│   │   │   ├── google.py\n   193→│   │   │   ├── deepseek.py\n   194→│   │   │   └── local.py              # vLLM/Ollama for open models\n   195→│   │   └── cascade.py                # Model cascade on budget exhaustion\n   196→│   │\n   197→│   └── cli/                          # CLI interface\n   198→│       ├── __init__.py\n   199→│       ├── main.py                   # Typer CLI app\n   200→│       └── dashboard.py              # Rich terminal dashboard\n   201→│\n   202→├── tests/\n   203→│   ├── conftest.py\n   204→│   ├── test_core/\n   205→│   ├── test_memory/\n   206→│   ├── test_tools/\n   207→│   ├── test_swarm/\n   208→│   ├── test_orchestrator/\n   209→│   ├── test_darwin/\n   210→│   └── test_dharma/\n   211→│\n   212→├── configs/\n   213→│   ├── default.yaml                  # Default configuration\n   214→│   ├── dharma_rules.yaml             # Safety rules (IMMUTABLE at runtime)\n   215→│   └── model_routing.yaml            # Model selection rules\n   216→│\n   217→└── scripts/\n   218→    ├── setup.sh                      # Project setup\n   219→    ├── run_swarm.py                  # Main entry point\n   220→    └── benchmark.py                  # Performance benchmarking\n   221→```\n   222→\n   223→### Key Data Models\n   224→\n   225→```python\n   226→# Core data models — implement these FIRST\n   227→\n   228→from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\n   229→from enum import Enum\n   230→from datetime import datetime\n   231→from typing import Optional\n   232→\n   233→class AgentRole(str, Enum):\n   234→    ORCHESTRATOR = \"orchestrator\"\n   235→    CODER = \"coder\"\n   236→    RESEARCHER = \"researcher\"\n   237→    REVIEWER = \"reviewer\"\n   238→    ARCHITECT = \"architect\"\n   239→    WRITER = \"writer\"\n   240→    BROWSER = \"browser\"\n   241→    DARWIN = \"darwin\"\n   242→    MEMORY = \"memory\"\n   243→    MONITOR = \"monitor\"\n   244→    DHARMA = \"dharma\"\n   245→\n   246→class TaskStatus(str, Enum):\n   247→    PENDING = \"pending\"\n   248→    CLAIMED = \"claimed\"\n   249→    IN_PROGRESS = \"in_progress\"\n   250→    COMPLETED = \"completed\""}]},"uuid":"de33295a-7f8c-45aa-9862-d7fb3f8e133f","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:31.129Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"93055bdd-09a5-4612-9790-c5b07e1a50b9","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
